cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.DS 

This paper is about efficient retrieval of relevant items based on highly-nonlinear models, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the design, analysis, and evaluation of algorithms for IR tasks. The paper also proposes a novel approach based on similarity graphs, which is a common technique in ML and pattern recognition. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers the theory, algorithms, and applications of ML. The paper also mentions applications in computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP), which are sub-fields of ML and could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language), respectively. Finally, the paper involves computational complexity and optimization, which are topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
